{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"570b1e48-42d0-410d-a824-13285598d252","content":"It's a small change. In your project file:\n\n**Remove** (or set to `false`):\n```xml\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nThat's the key switch — `MSTest.Sdk` 3.8.0 defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `UseVSTest` is **not** set to `true`.\n\n**Other things to be aware of:**\n\n1. **Running tests** — use `dotnet test` as before, but the underlying runner changes. CLI output format will differ slightly.\n2. **`dotnet test` compatibility** — add this if you want the new platform to work seamlessly with `dotnet test`:\n   ```xml\n   <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   ```\n3. **`.runsettings`** — most settings carry over, but VSTest-specific adapter settings may need updating.\n4. **CI/CD** — if you rely on `--logger trx`, it still works but requires the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` package (already included by `MSTest.Sdk`).\n5. **Test filters** — filter syntax changes slightly (e.g., `--filter` → `--filter` still works via compatibility layer, but native syntax uses `--treenode-filter`).\n\n**Minimal change:**\n```diff\n <Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n-    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n </Project>\n```\n\nAfter the change, run `dotnet test` to verify everything passes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b483807b-9415-4644-91ac-cbc486063832","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository doesn't have specific documentation about this migration. I'll answer based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk and the Microsoft.Testing.Platform migration.","outputTokens":464,"requestId":"702F:3F23E5:E2C6150:F8EC6A9:69F2A846"},"id":"b16aac4c-f4ff-4cc9-85fc-22dc573fd365","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:54:43.473Z","parentId":"19a30065-bcb9-49d7-8799-4907c135239a"}
